  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "This package documents credibility evidence for a CFD hemolysis prediction model of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump. The model has been applied in clinical research settings to support ventricular assist device (VAD) design decisions. A full 13-factor ASME V&V 40 assessment was conducted at Model Risk Level 5, with Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification performed across all operating conditions. Seven credibility factors were formally assessed; six were flagged as epistemic gaps. The model has been applied in clinical research to evaluate absolute hemolysis indices for Class III cardiac assist devices. All assessed factors achieved the required gradation levels under the Minimal profile declaration. Decision: Accepted.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-claim-001",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v3",
